parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gear Position Sensor Failure and Cruise Control Disengagement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear position sensor can cause the cruise control to disengage randomly, leading to sudden engine braking and rapid deceleration, which can increase the risk of rear-end collisions at high speeds.
symptoms: The gear indicator displays incorrect gear positions
and the motorcycle loses power and slows down rapidly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning fuel gauge can cause confusion and uncertainty about the fuel level, leading to potential safety risks if the motorcycle runs out of fuel unexpectedly.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays incorrect fuel levels
jumping from full to 1/4 tank or displaying random values.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning gear shifter can cause the motorcycle to jump into incorrect gears, leading to potential safety risks, especially when starting the bike or shifting up to sixth gear.
symptoms: and causes the motorcycle to jump into incorrect gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to unexpected gear shifts, loss of cruise control, and potentially even engine stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the rear brake switch can cause the brake fluid to leak, leading to a loss of braking performance, and potentially increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: rear brake light does not activate

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel gauge can lead to unexpected fuel depletion, causing the vehicle to run out of fuel, potentially leaving the driver stranded or causing an accident.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not read correctly or reliably
the fuel gauge does not move from the "full" position until the tank is almost empty
the fuel gauge suddenly drops to empty or near-empty
the vehicle runs out of fuel unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings and potentially causing the vehicle to run out of fuel unexpectedly.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not read correctly or reliably
the fuel gauge does not move from the "full" position until the tank is almost empty
the fuel gauge suddenly drops to empty or near-empty
the vehicle runs out of fuel unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning gear sensor can cause the vehicle to suddenly shift between 6th and 1st gear while cruise control is active, resulting in a loss of power and deactivation of cruise control, which can lead to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The gear sensor randomly switches between 6th and 1st gear while cruise control is active
